# Enterprise Documentation Standards

## **Inline Documentation Requirements**

### **XML Files (.keylayout, .xml)**
- **Comprehensive Headers**: Project overview, technical specifications, development history
- **Section Documentation**: Detailed explanations for each mapping section
- **Character Frequency Analysis**: Document character selection rationale
- **Technical Specifications**: Include all technical details and compatibility notes
- **Security Considerations**: Document security and compliance requirements

### **Markdown Files (.md)**
- **Project Overview**: Clear project description and key features
- **Technical Specifications**: Detailed technical requirements and system specs
- **Installation Instructions**: Step-by-step installation for all approaches
- **Troubleshooting**: Comprehensive problem-solving guides
- **Development Standards**: Code quality and maintenance standards

### **Configuration Files (.plist, .mdc)**
- **Purpose Documentation**: Clear explanation of file purpose and usage
- **Configuration Details**: Document all configuration options and settings
- **Dependencies**: List all dependencies and requirements
- **Usage Examples**: Provide clear usage examples and best practices

## **Documentation Quality Standards**

### **Enterprise-Grade Requirements**
- **Comprehensive Coverage**: Document all aspects of functionality
- **Technical Depth**: Include detailed technical specifications
- **Decision Rationale**: Explain why decisions were made
- **Maintenance History**: Track all changes and modifications
- **Security Documentation**: Include security considerations and compliance

### **Content Standards**
- **Clear Structure**: Use consistent formatting and organization
- **Technical Accuracy**: Ensure all technical information is correct
- **User-Friendly**: Make documentation accessible to all skill levels
- **Up-to-Date**: Keep documentation current with code changes
- **Searchable**: Use clear headings and keywords for easy navigation

## **Documentation Maintenance**

### **Update Requirements**
- **Code Changes**: Update documentation with every code change
- **Feature Additions**: Document new features immediately
- **Bug Fixes**: Update troubleshooting sections with new solutions
- **Version Updates**: Maintain version history and changelog

### **Quality Assurance**
- **Review Process**: Self-review all documentation before committing
- **Accuracy Verification**: Verify all technical information is correct
- **Completeness Check**: Ensure all aspects are documented
- **Consistency Review**: Maintain consistent style and format